         <abstract>
            <p>Upper bounds for the power of $p$ which divides the Fermat quotient $q_a = (a^{p-1} - 1)/p$ are obtained, and conditions are given which imply that $q_a \not\equiv 0 (\operatorname{mod} p)$. The results are in terms of the number of steps in a simple algorithm which determines the semiorder of $a (\operatorname{mod} p)$.</p>
          </abstract>
